  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic adversarial UnitOfAssurance package for ASME V&V 40 credibility assessment of CFD hemolysis prediction for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package targets weakness W-AR-05 (comparator absence or mismatch) via defeater type D3 (undercutting — inference method mismatch). The validation result for the primary hemolysis output comparison references a steady-state in vitro dataset as the experimental comparator, whereas the declared COU requires pulsatile flow conditions representative of VAD operation. One validation result is intentionally emitted without a comparedAgainst link (the rule-detection surface for W-AR-05). The mismatch is stated explicitly in the validation narrative: the comparator dataset was acquired under steady-state pump operation at fixed impeller speed, while the COU specifies five pulsatile flow-speed combinations spanning the VAD operating envelope. The inference from steady-state agreement to pulsatile hemolysis prediction is not supported by the validation evidence, constituting an undercutting defeater of the validation claim.",
