    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the submission on the basis of the output comparison result, which demonstrated NIH agreement within 18% against the steady-state in vitro dataset. The team did not flag the steady-state vs. pulsatile mismatch as a disqualifying gap, treating the steady-state comparator as sufficiently representative of VAD operating conditions. This acceptance rationale is flawed: the comparator is inappropriate for the declared COU (W-AR-05), and the inference from steady-state validation to pulsatile hemolysis prediction is an undercutting defeater (D3). All seven assessed credibility factors show achieved levels below required levels; six factors remain not assessed. The decision of Accepted is not supported by the evidence and reflects the targeted weakness.",
